Romeo🤍Juliet

An age-old vendetta between two powerful families erupts into bloodshed. An age-old vendetta between two powerful families erupts into bloodshed. A group of masked Montagues risk further conflict by gatecrashing a Capulet party. A young lovesick Romeo Montague falls instantly in love with Juliet Capulet, who is due to marry her father's choice, the County Paris.

The play is set in the city of Verona, Italy, and revolves around the love affair between two young members of feuding noble families, the Montagues (Romeo's family) and the Capulets (Juliet's family). Romeo Montague and Juliet Capulet meet at a masquerade ball and fall deeply in love at first sight. Despite the intense rivalry between their families, they secretly marry the next day, hoping their union will bring an end to the long-standing feud.
